climbs.name: Weber
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan, Kenn Kenaga & Eric Tipton 7/98

content.description: Goes up 30 feet nice hand jams and patina on the face on either side, head for the shelf.
content.protection:
Big cams up to #2-3 Camalot 1 Bolt at top.

Note: The guide book says it summits but we could not find bolts and there does not appear to be any natural protection.
content.location: Farthest west (leftmost) hand crack. Nice quick warm up with a walk off on the back.

content.description: The crux comes at the 3rd bolt moving towards the 4th. The climb is well protected with solid bolts. The climb starts out on the face and moves out onto an arete glances off the roof then back on to the face to the summit.
content.location: The striking arete on the southwest corner of the rock.

climbs.name: Kahanna
climbs.fa: Eric Tipton, Kenn Kenaga & Pat Brennan 7/98

content.description: The crux is getting up the ramp and under the roof from their it gets technical. The amazing finger crack is your reward for getting past the roof. The ramp is very balancy think sequence. This route is awesome I will definitly be hiking up there again to do this one. The face above the bolt is a little loose so belayer beware.
content.protection: 1 Bolt at the bottom and small protection .4 C4 Cammolots Orange & Yellow Metolius TCU.up to 1"  Chains at the top.
content.location:
The obvious crack just right

Migs Over Moscow

. Look for the large flake and the angled ramp below the striking roof.

climbs.name: Barbara Ann
climbs.fa: Pat Brennan, Kenn Kanaga, Eric Tipton, 7/1998

content.description: Splitter dihedral crack that starts wide, narrows to hands, and finishes with a fun roof.  Upper part still quite covered with lichen.  A very nice climb once that cleans up.
